cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.BIO, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the use of kernel-based learning algorithms to improve rankings of functionally related enzymes based on similarities in their sequences, structures, and surfaces. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of databases and annotations also suggests a connection to database systems (cs.DB). The focus on biological function and the Enzyme Commission classification hierarchy suggests a connection to bioinformatics (cs.BIO) and computational biology (cs.CE).
